A pregnant woman and nine others were injured during a stampede at the Imo State Governor Emeka Ihedioha’s inauguration yesterday in Owerri. A member of the medical team for the inauguration, Dr Francis Igwe, confirmed the figure in Owerri. The stampede resulted from a huge crowd, which besieged the Dan Anyiam Stadium, venue of the inauguration, Igwe, however, said the victims were revived. The medical expert told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) that the medical team led by Dr. Vin Udokwu ws proactive to handle the situation. He said: “When we saw the crowd, we suspected that there may be an emergency situation; we quickly put our personnel and equipment together just to get ready.” Members of the Red Cross Society were also seen assisting in the rescue operations during the stampede. Before the inauguration, a woman had fainted and was carried away from the field by the medical personnel on a stretcher. Igwe said that all situations were controlled.